<br>
Having your children raised by those not close to the child, foments a atmosphere of apathy.  People who work for a government agency have too much going on to spend any sort of quality time with each child in their care.  Children need to know they are loved, and that people are interested in what they do and think.<br>
<br>
I never once suggested that children must not be influenced from outside the home, it can't be done.  My point is that if you take an important role in their upbringing, you create a solid base for them to be able to judge the value of outside influences.<br>
<br>
